FuelType.name: FuelType
FuelType.description: Represents information about the additional fuel types defined by a customer.

Description.description: The developer name of the record.

DeveloperName.description: The developer name of the record. For custom fuels in the FuelTypeSustnUom, StnryAssetEnrgyUse, and VehicleAssetEnrgyUse objects, if the NamespacePrefix exists then this value in combination with {NamespacePrefix}_custom_ is used; for example, ft_package_custom_wood, else, this value in combination with custom_ is used; for example, custom_wood.

IsActive.description: Indicates whether the fuel type is active and can be used (true) or not (false).

IsStationaryAssetFuel.description: Indicates whether the fuel is used in stationary assets (true) or not (false).

IsVehicleAssetFuel.description: Indicates whether the fuel is used in a vehicle asset (true) or not (false).

Language.description: The language associated with this record.

MasterLabel.description: The label assigned to this object.

NamespacePrefix.description: The namespace prefix that is associated with this object. Limit: 15 characters.
